g.title: j3440568300
g.text: Give me a reason not to hate Entrati
And the whole damn future you come from

g.title: j988327984
g.text: Check boolean LettieCavia

g.title: j799104964
g.text: Because as far as I can tell
He's an animal abusing cabrón

g.text: true

g.title: j988327984->j101638081

g.title: j467645667
g.text: I don't disagree. I hate Entrati as much as you do. But the future is worth fighting for, even if it'd be better without him in it.

g.title: j942514260
g.text: Entrati isn't all bad, he's trying to fix his mistakes. And anybody who's capable of love has something worth saving in them, IMO.

g.title: j3465483868
g.text: Yikes. I know when a conversation is going to go poorly. I'm out. [End.]

g.title: j3656667717
g.text: And none of this "greater good" pendejadas
And your whole stinking future can get screwed as far as I'm concerned

g.title: j101638081->j3656667717
g.text: true

g.title: j4273525604
g.text: Because from where I sit
That cabrón thinks he is a god and he let one loose
And now it's all our problems to deal with
So him and his future can get screwed as far as I'm concerned

g.title: j101638081->j4273525604
g.text: false

g.title: j3939033661
g.text: He is TRASH
And the future is TRASH

g.title: j3451365369
g.text: Love?
Who could possibly love someone like that

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j1244706505
g.text: I'm from the future. Do you think I'm trash?

g.title: j2084666020
g.text: Just because you hate one guy doesn't mean the whole future is garbage.

g.title: j811014379
g.text: His name's Loid. Sort of a... workplace romance, you could say.

g.title: j3615065182
g.text: He had a family. Wife, kids, grandkids now.

g.title: j1876341143
g.text: it may not be ugly to you
But it is WRONG
It is not what the gods intended
He tampered with it all

g.title: j2107289513
g.text: ¿Ay, sí?
I did not see Loid here with him

g.title: j1406745991
g.text: You said HAD
What do you mean, HAD

g.title: j776436305
g.text: Check boolean LettieReligion2

g.title: j1128490856
g.text: Loid is still in the future, guarding Entrati's lab. He's been there for centuries.

g.title: j963696646
g.text: Entrati abandoned Loid like he abandons everybody.

g.title: j589855851
g.text: Well, the issue is, his daughter thinks he's lost, and is searching for him. It's complicated.

g.title: j1812514312
g.text: I mean, I'm sure he loved them at one point...

g.title: j1369070846
g.text: I've got a warning light going off in - um - I have to go. [End.]

g.title: j2365332947
g.text: If he never angered Xipe Totec, this Man in the Wall, none of your future would exist

g.text: Used and tossed away
I bet not the first time he's done it
¿Verdad?

g.text: He abandoned his family
Let me guess
He's done it another time hasn't he

g.title: j1116369003
g.text: The void would not have been unleashed, ¿no?

Your life would have been happier

g.title: j598911108
g.text: There's no way of knowing what could have been. In fact, without the Tenno, all of humanity might be gone by now, wiped out by the Sentients.

g.title: j1533732539
g.text: You're right, but I can't change what's been done. Not at that scale. I'm doing my best to save who and what I can.

g.title: j2791275366
g.text: Yeah... he abandoned his family. He had a wife, kids, and now grandkids.

g.title: j4176507548->j2791275366
g.text: true

g.title: j305216245
g.text: Look, it doesn't matter. He doesn't define the future.

g.title: j4176507548->j305216245
g.text: true

g.title: j2114124668
g.text: Yeah... he abandoned the Cavia, the animals he experimented on and accidentally made intelligent.

g.title: j3956439183
g.text: Sentients?

g.title: j2318952225
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j2285023139
g.text: Boolean LettieEntratiFamily is now true.

g.title: j3050647161
g.text: But he HAS defined it don't you see
It's because of him that everything is the way it is

g.title: j3246520567
g.text: If I ever see him again-
I am going to KILL him, and let you reset the world so I can do it AGAIN

g.title: j1150053678

g.title: j1198170299
g.text: Sí
I am just angry, lo siento
This is not your fault and you are not garbage

g.title: j3187474806
g.text: You are making my point, ¿no?
He is trash and the future is trash

g.title: j2371855287
g.text: Boolean LettieCavia is now true.

g.title: j3847830476
g.text: A synthetic race made by the Orokin and the future human society to terraform a planet called Tau, because we were ruining Earth.

g.title: j2577231822
g.text: A synthetic race made by the Orokin and future human society who waged war on us after they were made.

g.title: j2233391658
g.text: You are like me
Just a medic keeping as many lives from joining La Flaca too early as possible

g.title: j2776991702
g.text: More mortals playing at being gods
These orokin are trash
All that power and technology
And they could not save our planet

g.title: j1066923992
g.text: More mortals playing at being gods
These orokin are trash
The sentients lashed out at their creators

g.title: j339122421
g.text: But Entrati can go screw a brick sideways

g.title: j3022900112
g.text: Instead they wanted to make a golden new home somewhere else
Where they could be the only gods, far away from the Father and Mother

g.title: j2868520347
g.text: Why?

g.title: j4137157349
g.text: Boolean LettieReligion3 is now true.

g.title: j1718426170
g.text: Because the Orokin sent them there to terraform a new planet, Tau, and the Sentients were worried that we'd ruin that one, too.

g.title: j268760277
g.text: Because they're just as egotistical, violent, and evil as the Orokin.

g.title: j1787631430
g.text: Father and Mother? You mean Sol and Lua?

g.title: j3586171895
g.text: Sol and Lua aren't gods, Lettie... they're just a star and a rock...

g.title: j2009274870
g.text: De tal palo, tal astilla
Humans making a race in their image
Thinking they are the Father and Mother
Disgusting

g.title: j1649853383
g.text: Sí
They are something special, deep down, something more to us than just what they are at first glance

g.title: j1636064988
g.text: Sí
And your Man in the Wall is just a collection of atoms
And you are just a person with nothing special about them except what was done to them

g.title: j1494452677
g.text: Do you believe in the unseen, ¿babas?
Do you believe in something beyond the world we can measure?

g.title: j2234506481
g.text: Check boolean ReligionNone

g.title: j4036846596
g.text: I've told you already, I don't believe in anything.

g.title: j2234506481->j4036846596

g.text: No. If you can't measure it, it doesn't exist.

g.title: j2234506481->j1556192502

g.title: j4293766149
g.text: Maybe? I think it's just science we don't understand yet.

g.title: j2234506481->j4293766149

g.title: j2701349784
g.text: Of course I do. I'm a product of the Void.

g.title: j2234506481->j2701349784
